00:09:15.254 --> 00:09:17.890
Eight shows into
my run in Australia,

00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:18.924
uh, I'm on fire.

00:09:18.924 --> 00:09:21.059
My insides are burning.
It's awful.

00:09:21.059 --> 00:09:22.895
I go to the doctor,
they give me some drugs,

00:09:22.895 --> 00:09:24.596
which I--oh, my gosh.
I remember these.

00:09:24.596 --> 00:09:26.331
Uh, they had to--they had to
give me some drugs

00:09:26.331 --> 00:09:28.433
because I was in so much pain,
I forgot even about drugs.

00:09:28.433 --> 00:09:30.903
I forgot that there were--like,
I was in "Kill me" pain.

00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:33.071
I was literally like the dog--
just end this.

00:09:33.071 --> 00:09:35.107
Just fucking end it.
I was in so much pain.

00:09:35.107 --> 00:09:37.242
They give me, um,
I don't know, whatever.

00:09:37.242 --> 00:09:38.744
Some sort of pain reliever.

00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:40.112
And then they take a photo
of my insides,

00:09:40.112 --> 00:09:41.781
and then they wake me up,
and they say,

00:09:41.781 --> 00:09:44.449
"You have tumors in your
stomach--you have cancer."

00:09:44.449 --> 00:09:46.117
Fuck.
I was on my way to a comeback.

00:09:46.117 --> 00:09:49.354
Um, so that's what they said.
You have a--

00:09:49.354 --> 00:09:50.622
but it was in Australia,
so I have to say,

00:09:50.622 --> 00:09:51.957
and I'm not saying get cancer.

00:09:51.957 --> 00:09:55.027
I'm against it.
I'm against cancer.

00:09:55.027 --> 00:09:57.596
I just want to come out right
now and say I'm against cancer.

00:09:57.596 --> 00:09:59.264
I don't want you to get it.

00:09:59.264 --> 00:10:01.266
Should you think you have it,

00:10:01.266 --> 00:10:02.968
go to Australia
to get the diagnosis,

00:10:02.968 --> 00:10:05.204
because just the way
they say "cancer"

00:10:05.204 --> 00:10:09.274
sounds a tiny bit less bad.

00:10:09.274 --> 00:10:11.810
That's all. "Cancer."
It just goes up at the end.

00:10:11.810 --> 00:10:13.612
It just--"Cancer, mate.
You have cancer, mate."

00:10:13.612 --> 00:10:14.613
They say "mate" a lot.

00:10:14.613 --> 00:10:15.714
It just feels cheerier,

00:10:15.714 --> 00:10:16.715
like you're doing it together.

00:10:16.715 --> 00:10:17.816
"Hey, you got cancer, mate."

00:10:17.816 --> 00:10:19.384
"We all do?"
"No, you do."

00:10:19.384 --> 00:10:21.487
Anyway, cancer. They told me.
I had it.

00:10:21.487 --> 00:10:22.487
Uh, they thought I did.

00:10:22.487 --> 00:10:24.056
I had tumors in my stomach,

00:10:24.056 --> 00:10:25.557
they weren't sure what they
were, but they were--

00:10:25.557 --> 00:10:27.492
there was a cluster of tumors,
right?

00:10:27.492 --> 00:10:28.994
Just really--a lot of Rs.
A lot of--

00:10:28.994 --> 00:10:31.330
You find out there's a lot of Rs
in cancer.

00:10:31.330 --> 00:10:33.332
"Cluster," "tumor"--
lot of Rs.

00:10:33.332 --> 00:10:34.666
So I-I--

00:10:34.666 --> 00:10:36.635
They think I have cancer,
and they say,

00:10:36.635 --> 00:10:38.670
"You have to go home,"
and I was so high

00:10:38.670 --> 00:10:39.671
on whatever it was they gave me,
I'm like,

00:10:39.671 --> 00:10:41.640
"To my apartment in Australia?"

00:10:41.640 --> 00:10:42.808
And they go, "No, to America."

00:10:42.808 --> 00:10:45.143
You have to take
your cancer home.

00:10:45.143 --> 00:10:46.745
You have to take it home.
Can't have it there.

00:10:46.745 --> 00:10:48.480
They--they don't want you
dying there.

00:10:48.480 --> 00:10:51.817
So, um, uh,
so I say, "All right."

00:10:51.817 --> 00:10:53.818
And they, uh, they say,
"But you're gonna be in pain

00:10:53.818 --> 00:10:55.321
"until you get to the hospital.

00:10:55.321 --> 00:10:57.322
"You need to get there within
the next 72 hours.

00:10:57.322 --> 00:10:59.158
But here is a box of OxyContin."

00:10:59.158 --> 00:11:01.193
I'm like, that could
be a mistake.

00:11:01.193 --> 00:11:02.928
A box.
Not just a few.

00:11:02.928 --> 00:11:05.263
A fucking box.
Like, with trays.

00:11:05.263 --> 00:11:06.532
Do you understand?

00:11:06.532 --> 00:11:07.866
We're talking about
a street value

00:11:07.866 --> 00:11:09.367
of about a million dollars!

00:11:09.367 --> 00:11:11.002
To a drug addict!

00:11:11.002 --> 00:11:12.838
Who's already high from whatever
it is they gave them--

00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:14.873
I went out and bought a hat.

00:11:14.873 --> 00:11:16.842
So...

00:11:16.842 --> 00:11:18.944
Here's how high I was.

00:11:18.944 --> 00:11:20.846
I had my manager with me.
I said, "Take the pills.

00:11:20.846 --> 00:11:22.548
"Give 'em to me, and let's be
responsible about this.

00:11:22.548 --> 00:11:24.350
"I just want to get home.
I want to see my family.

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.785
If I'm gonna die, fair enough,
but I just want to get home."

00:11:26.785 --> 00:11:30.121
So, uh, I go, uh, to, uh,
the airport,

00:11:30.121 --> 00:11:32.024
and everything's fine, except
for I accidently put a knife

00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:33.726
in my backpack.
That's--you don't--

00:11:33.726 --> 00:11:35.460
you're not allowed to take
a knife through customs.

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:37.563
I don't know if I'm sharing
anything new with you guys,

00:11:37.563 --> 00:11:40.232
but no knives at customs
on an international flight.

00:11:40.232 --> 00:11:41.734
They don't care for it.

00:11:41.734 --> 00:11:43.969
So I had a knife in my backpack,
and the lady goes--

00:11:43.969 --> 00:11:45.370
she was very nice,
and she said,

00:11:45.370 --> 00:11:46.639
"Sir, this is a knife."

00:11:46.639 --> 00:11:49.742
And I said to her,
"I have cancer."

00:11:52.577 --> 00:11:56.882
She literally goes,
"Uh..."

00:11:56.882 --> 00:11:58.417
I don't know
what the next sentence is.

00:11:58.417 --> 00:12:00.919
Like, literally, I don't know
what to say to you.

00:12:00.919 --> 00:12:03.255
So she's like, "Well, you still
have to leave the knife,

00:12:03.255 --> 00:12:04.423
but I'll give you a hug."

00:12:04.423 --> 00:12:06.759
So...

00:12:06.759 --> 00:12:09.327
My--my manager's with me,

00:12:09.327 --> 00:12:11.163
so that's my thing.
I'm like, "Just make sure

00:12:11.163 --> 00:12:12.898
"that I don't overuse
the drugs, 'cause I could,

00:12:12.898 --> 00:12:14.566
"and because I'm dying,
I probably don't care.

00:12:14.566 --> 00:12:16.434
"So make me care and don't let
me take all the drugs,

00:12:16.434 --> 00:12:18.570
'cause I don't want to show up
at home being that guy."

00:12:18.570 --> 00:12:19.938
So I get on the airplane,

00:12:19.938 --> 00:12:21.840
and they stick my manager
in fucking economy

00:12:21.840 --> 00:12:23.508
and they put me in first class,
so I know I'm dying, right?

00:12:23.508 --> 00:12:24.743
I know it's a Make-A-Wish thing.

00:12:24.743 --> 00:12:26.345
"Put him in first class,

00:12:26.345 --> 00:12:27.779
it's probably the last time
he'll be on a plane."

00:12:27.779 --> 00:12:30.582
So they throw him
in fucking baggage

00:12:30.582 --> 00:12:33.084
and I'm sitting in a throne or
a--you know, whatever it is.

00:12:33.084 --> 00:12:35.521
Just this massive thing
where they give you backrubs.

00:12:35.521 --> 00:12:37.789
And I'm sitting next to a guy
who I don't know,

00:12:37.789 --> 00:12:40.092
who turns out to be this drummer
for the band Switchfoot.

00:12:40.092 --> 00:12:41.426
Do you guys know
Switchfoot at all?

00:12:41.426 --> 00:12:42.761
Yeah? Yeah?

00:12:42.761 --> 00:12:43.962
That's usually
the response I get.

00:12:43.962 --> 00:12:44.964
Yeah...

00:12:44.964 --> 00:12:46.298
So, uh, anyway--

00:12:46.298 --> 00:12:47.933
they're a fine band,
they're a fine band.

00:12:47.933 --> 00:12:48.933
I don't know them,
but I know who they are.

00:12:48.933 --> 00:12:50.635
But I--I know that they surf,

00:12:50.635 --> 00:12:52.604
and I know they're Christian,
and that's all I know.

00:12:52.604 --> 00:12:53.806
Probably couldn't sing a song,

00:12:53.806 --> 00:12:55.040
but the guy's super nice,

00:12:55.040 --> 00:12:57.275
the drummer,
and so we start talking,

00:12:57.275 --> 00:12:59.044
I say, "Look, I'm gonna ask you
a really weird favor,

00:12:59.044 --> 00:13:00.946
"but I'm dying--maybe--
probably--

00:13:00.946 --> 00:13:02.314
"and, uh, I have to take
these pills,

00:13:02.314 --> 00:13:03.715
"and would you give them to me
and not let me

00:13:03.715 --> 00:13:04.984
"take more than I need
and make sure

00:13:04.984 --> 00:13:06.651
I take them when
I'm supposed to?"

00:13:06.651 --> 00:13:08.120
And he said, "Yeah, sure."
I said, "Thank you."

00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:10.288
Also, if I get up--
like, if I rub your chest

00:13:10.288 --> 00:13:11.823
or walk around the plane, or--

00:13:11.823 --> 00:13:13.726
I don't know if any of you have
ever been on OxyContin,

00:13:13.726 --> 00:13:15.827
but it's not bad.
Yeah, you feel--

00:13:15.827 --> 00:13:17.463
you're friendly,
and you like conversations,

00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:20.232
and you want to talk to everyone
about everything, and you also--

00:13:20.232 --> 00:13:22.134
It has this amazing thing
that never happens to me

00:13:22.134 --> 00:13:24.636
in real life--it actually makes
you want to listen to people.

00:13:24.636 --> 00:13:26.806
So...

00:13:26.806 --> 00:13:28.740
Like, you're genuinely
interested in weird shit.

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:30.142
What kind of buttons are those?

00:13:30.142 --> 00:13:32.411
"On my--on my shirt?"
Yeah. They seem neat.

00:13:32.411 --> 00:13:35.914
All right.

00:13:35.914 --> 00:13:38.350
Anyway, the guy was super nice
and I said, "Would you make sure

00:13:38.350 --> 00:13:40.485
I don't overuse these?"
And then I passed out

00:13:40.485 --> 00:13:42.354
and I slept the whole flight.

00:13:42.354 --> 00:13:44.656
You know.
Uh, and, uh,

00:13:44.656 --> 00:13:47.025
so, we get to Los Angeles,

00:13:47.025 --> 00:13:49.862
and, uh--and uh,
so it's cool.

00:13:49.862 --> 00:13:51.697
I'm sitting next to a guy
from a band.

00:13:51.697 --> 00:13:52.998
That's neat, and he says,

00:13:52.998 --> 00:13:54.533
"Let me walk
you to baggage claim."

00:13:54.533 --> 00:13:57.202
So the drummer from Switchfoot
walks me to baggage claim,

00:13:57.202 --> 00:13:59.004
gets my bags for me,
and then he goes,

00:13:59.004 --> 00:14:01.707
"Hey, man, I just want to tell
you that I love you.

00:14:01.707 --> 00:14:03.275
"I said a prayer for you.

00:14:03.275 --> 00:14:04.343
You're gonna be fine."

00:14:04.343 --> 00:14:05.544
And I was like, wow.

00:14:05.544 --> 00:14:07.178
And I bent down
to pick up my bags,

00:14:07.178 --> 00:14:11.783
and I turned around,
and he was fucking gone.

00:14:11.783 --> 00:14:13.953
Gone--not, like,
oh, in a crowd.

00:14:13.953 --> 00:14:17.289
Like, fucking--
there was nobody--

00:14:17.289 --> 00:14:20.458
he was gone!

00:14:20.458 --> 00:14:21.559
I was like, fuck!

00:14:21.559 --> 00:14:24.029
Did I dream that?

00:14:24.029 --> 00:14:25.230
Were these my last moments?

00:14:25.230 --> 00:14:27.699
I had a lucid dream?

00:14:27.699 --> 00:14:32.070
Why the guy from Switchfoot?

00:14:32.070 --> 00:14:34.073
Thank you.

